==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Pate
<hw>Pate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. LG. & Prov. G.
<ets>pattkopf</ets>, <ets>patzkopf</ets>, scabby head; <ets>patt</ets>,
<ets>patz</ets>, scab + <ets>kopf</ets> head.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>The head of a person; the top, or crown, of the head.</def>
<mark>[Now generally used in contempt or ridicule.]</mark><-- esp., bald
pate -->⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>His mischief shall return upon his own head, and his violent
dealing shall come down upon his own <qex>pate</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Ps.
vii. 16.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Fat paunches have lean <qex>pate</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The skin of a calf's head.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pated</ent>⟦br⟧
